lthough now no longer associated with that name. Initial <i>H-</i> tended to be added and dropped rather capriciously, leading to many doublets (  compare for example  Esther   and   Hester  ). It is also sometimes used as a short form of   Eleanor  , to which, however, it is unrelated."],"variants":[{"name":"Eleanor","meanings":["From an Old French respelling of the Old Provençal name <i>Alienor</i>. This has sometimes been taken as a derivative of   Helen  , but it is more probably of Germanic derivation (the first element being <i>ali</i> ‘other, foreign’ the second is obscure). The name was introduced to England by  Eleanor of Aquitaine  (  1122–1204 ), who came from Aquitaine in south-west France to be the wife of  King Henry II . It was also borne by Eleanor of Provence, the wife of  Henry III , and Eleanor of Castile, wife of  Edward I ."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"Ellen was born about 1560, in Swalcliffe, Oxfordshire, England, United Kingdom. She married William Faxon in 1575, in Swalcliffe, Oxfordshire, England, United Kingdom. They were the parents of at least 1 son. She died on 7 November 1600, in her hometown, at the age of 41."},"et":{"Abt 1560–7 November 1600":"umbes 1560–7. november 1600","1555–1613":"1555–1613","1600–1680":"1600–1680","1560–1600":"1560–1600","Abt 1560":"umbes 1560","1613":"1613","1600":"1600","1555":"1555","Abt 1575":"1575","7 November 1600":"7. november 1600","1560":"1560","1680":"1680","Swalcliffe, Oxford, England":"Swalcliffe, Oxfordshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Swalcliffe, Oxfordshire, England":"Swalcliffe, Oxfordshire, England"},"fi":{"Abt 1560–7 November 1600":"noin 1560–7. marraskuuta 1600","1555–1613":"1555–1613","1600–1680":"1600–1680","1560–1600":"1560–1600","Abt 1560":"noin 1560","1613":"1613","1600":"1600","1555":"1555","Abt 1575":"1575","7 November 1600":"7. marraskuuta 1600","1560":"1560","1680":"1680","Swalcliffe, Oxford, England":"Swalcliffe, Oxfordshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Swalcliffe, Oxfordshire, Eng